-- Regression test for an unsolved IntrMap type-inference bug.
--
-- The desugar-inserted IntrMap ($intrmap) is used for bracket-accessor
-- broadcast such as `.[0:2].0 xs`. Its synth-mode typing in
-- Frontend/Typecheck.hs assigns fresh existentials `map_elem_`,
-- `map_result_`, `map_container_` and checks the function and receiver
-- against `a -> b` and `f a` respectively.
--
-- When the broadcast tail is a tuple index selector (`.0`, `.1`, ...)
-- and the receiver is `[(T, U, ...)]`, the check of the lambda body
-- against the fresh `b` fails to solve `b` from the tuple field's
-- inferred type. `b` leaks to serialization codegen, which emits
--
--     cannot serialize type: map_result_<N>
--
-- Broadcasting a *record field* accessor (`.name`, `.age`) resolves
-- correctly because the record's row-polymorphic check pins the field
-- type. Broadcasting `.0` over a tuple does not.
--
-- This test is a PIN: the build is expected to fail with the
-- `map_result_` diagnostic. When the underlying inference bug is
-- fixed, this test will start passing the build and the grep will
-- come up empty -- delete the test and move the pattern into
-- pattern-corpus / pattern-getters as a positive case.

module main (foo)

foo :: Str -> <IO> [(Int, Int)]
foo path = do
  let xs = [(1, 2), (3, 4), (5, 6)]
  @savem (.[0:2].0 xs) path
  xs
